### .oxlintrc.json
```json
{
  "$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oxc-project/oxc/main/npm/oxlint/configuration_schema.json",
  "ignorePatterns": [
    "node_modules/",
    ".engin/",
    "wwwroot/",
    "bin/",
    "obj/",
    "dist/",
    "SampleFiles/",
    "coverage/",
    "package-lock.json"
  ],
  "categories": {
    "correctness": "error"
  },
  "rules": {
    "no-console": "off"
  }
}

```
Fix two config issues:

1. **`scripts/copy-assets.mjs` has a bare `catch {}` that silently swallows ALL errors**, not just the intended ENOENT (file not found). The `copyFile` call for `src/app.css` is wrapped in a try/catch whose comment says 'If src/app.css doesn't exist, skip silently.' But the bare catch also hides permission errors, disk full errors, etc. Fix by catching only ENOENT and re-throwing all other errors:
   ```js
   try {
     await copyFile(srcPath, destPath);
   } catch (err) {
     if (err.code !== 'ENOENT') throw err;
   }
   ```

2. **Dead ignore patterns in `.prettierignore` and `.oxlintrc.json`:** Both files ignore root `dist/` but the actual build output is at `wwwroot/dist/`. The root `dist/` directory does not exist and is never created. Update both files:
   - In `.prettierignore`: change `dist/` to `wwwroot/dist/` (keep all other patterns the same).
   - In `.oxlintrc.json` `ignorePatterns` array: change `"dist/"` to `"wwwroot/dist/"` (keep all other patterns the same).

Verification: Run `npm run build` (triggers copy-assets.mjs) to confirm no error. Run `npm run format:check` and `npm run lint` to confirm the updated ignore patterns work. Confirm `wwwroot/dist/` is still properly ignored.

